      "content": "i mean \"long term\" doesn't really help the people losing their livelihoods right now though. do u think it's actually possible to be \"equitable\" or is that just something politicians say to make the bill sound better while they're basically just picking winners and losers? like, can you actually make a solar job a direct replacement for a high-paying coal job in a rural area?",
